<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16593] Unify HTable with AP</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16593</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, HTable has two ways to deal with request,  one is call RPC directly, it is used to processed single action request such as Get, Delete, Append, Increment.  Another one is through AP to deal with multi action requests, such as batch, mutation etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue is to unify them with AP only. It has some benefits, for example we could implements async interface easily with AP,  and we could make the client logic more clear just use AP to communicate with Server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14703&quot; title=&quot;HTable.mutateRow does not collect stats&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-14703&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-14703&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has done some work (unify mutate and checkAndMutate with AP)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
